`crates/steno` is the compiler crate for `.steno` source: it compiles a stroke-annotated DSL into Plover dictionaries, LSP snippets, block-editor keystroke events, and diagnostic/viz JSON. Depending on this crate buys a complete, corpus-validated `parse → expand → render/snippet` pipeline; nothing outside `src/` is meant to be imported, and `tests/` exists purely to pin behavior against the real `dict.steno` corpus.

The crate has two children of consequence — `src/` (the pipeline and its `bin/` I/O consumers) and `tests/` (integration coverage) — plus a stray `nvim.log` that is a runtime artifact, not source. The coupling between them is one-directional and corpus-driven: `tests/` hardcodes specific strokes, counts, and thresholds from `dict.steno`/`dict.infinite.steno`, so any edit to that corpus (or to the `terminal`-flag fixup order, or to `editor::Event`'s variant shape) inside `src/` requires auditing the matching tests across multiple files, not just the first one that fails. `tests/` never feeds back into `src/`.

Invariant spanning the crate: everything is `Result`-based with no panics (enforced in `src/`, verified in `tests/`), and stroke text is always canonicalized by `render_stroke` before comparison — no code anywhere should assume string-identity round-tripping of raw stroke text.

No `intent.md` exists for this directory, so no divergence can be assessed.